div.div:
This can be read as : kindB is a Composite and has one input pin "b" and one output pin "c",
and two other parts kindE and KindF. KindE has one input pin "g" and one output pin "h".
KindF has one input pin "j" and one output pin "k".
KindB wires up its two children, of type kindE and kindF.
The "input" pin "b" is wired to pin "g". Pin "k" is wired up to "output" pin "c".
Input pin "b" comes from the outside and output pin "c" goes to the outside (we cannot know
what is outside of this part (in this view). Input pin "b" acts like (has the functionality of) a "source"
and output pin "c" acts like a sink. If we keep going, we can say - at THIS level - "g" and "j" act
like sinks of events and "h" and "k" act like sources of events.
